id.description: /** Unique ID for the node. Either provided by the application, or generated by the grid if not. */

groupData.description: /** If using row grouping, contains the group values for this group. */

aggData.description: /** If using row grouping and aggregation, contains the aggregation data. */

parent.description: /** The parent node to this node, or empty if top level */

level.description: /** How many levels this node is from the top when grouping. */

uiLevel.description: /** How many levels this node is from the top when grouping in the UI (only different to `parent` when `groupRemoveSingleChildren=true`)*/

group.description: /** `true` if this node is a group node (ie has children) */

dragging.description: /** `true` if this row is getting dragged */

master.description: /** `true` if this row is a master row, part of master / detail (ie row can be expanded to show detail) */

detail.description: /** `true` if this row is a detail row, part of master / detail (ie child row of an expanded master row)*/

detailNode.description: /** If this row is a master row that was expanded, this points to the associated detail row. */

detailGridInfo.description: /** If master detail, this contains details about the detail grid */

leafGroup.description: /** `true` if this node is a group and the group is the bottom level in the tree. */

firstChild.description: /** `true` if this is the first child in this group. Changes when data is sorted. */

lastChild.description: /** `true` if this is the last child in this group. Changes when data is sorted. */

childIndex.description: /** Index of this row with respect to its parent when grouping. Changes when data is sorted. */

rowIndex.description: /** The current row index. If the row is filtered out or in a collapsed group, this value will be `null`. */

rowPinned.description: /** Either 'top' or 'bottom' if row pinned, otherwise `undefined` or `null`. */

sticky.description: /** When true, this row will appear in the top */

stickyRowTop.description: /** If row is pinned, then pinnedRowTop is used rather than rowTop */

quickFilterAggregateText.description: /** If using quick filter, stores a string representation of the row for searching against. */

footer.description: /** `true` if row is a footer. Footers have `group = true` and `footer = true`. */

field.description: /** The field we are grouping on eg 'country'. */

rowGroupColumn.description: /** The row group column used for this group, e.g. the Country column instance. */

key.description: /** The key for the group eg Ireland, UK, USA */

stub.description: /** Used by server-side row model. `true` if this row node is a stub. A stub is a placeholder row with loading icon while waiting from row to be loaded. */

failedLoad.description: /** Used by server side row model, true if this row node failed a load */

needsRefresh.description: /** Used by server side row model, true if this row node requires reload */

needsVerify.description: /** Used by server side row model, true if this node needs verified by the server  */

allLeafChildren.description: /** All lowest level nodes beneath this node, no groups. */

childrenAfterGroup.description: /** Children of this group. If multi levels of grouping, shows only immediate children. */

childrenAfterAggFilter.description: /** Aggregated and re-filtered children of this group. */

allChildrenCount.description: /** Number of children and grand children. */

childrenMapped.description: /** Children mapped by the pivot columns. */

childStore.description: /** Server Side Row Model Only - the children are in an infinite cache. */

sibling.description: /** If using footers, reference to the footer node for this group. */

rowHeight.description: /** The height, in pixels, of this row */

rowHeightEstimated.description:
/** Dynamic row heights are done on demand, only when row is visible. However for row virtualisation
     * we need a row height to do the 'what rows are in viewport' maths. So we assign a row height to each
     * row based on defaults and rowHeightEstimated=true, then when the row is needed for drawing we do
     * the row height calculation and set rowHeightEstimated=false.*/

displayed.description:
/** This will be `true` if it has a rowIndex assigned, otherwise `false`.
     */

rowTop.description: /** The row top position in pixels. */

oldRowTop.description:
/** The top pixel for this row last time, makes sense if data set was ordered or filtered,
     * it is used so new rows can animate in from their old position. */

daemon.description:
/** `true` if this node is a daemon. This means row is not part of the model. Can happen when then
     * the row is selected and then the user sets a different ID onto the node. The nodes is then
     * representing a different entity, so the selection controller, if the node is selected, takes
     * a copy where daemon=true. */

selectable.description: /** `true` by default - can be overridden via gridOptions.isRowSelectable(rowNode) */

___cacheData.description: /** Used by the value service, stores values for a particular change detection turn. */

___objectId.description:
/** Used by sorting service - to give deterministic sort to groups. Previously we
     * just id for this, however id is a string and had slower sorting compared to numbers. */

alreadyRendered.description: /** `true` when nodes with the same id are being removed and added as part of the same batch transaction */

setData.description: /** Replaces the data on the `rowNode`. When complete, the grid will refresh the the entire rendered row if it is showing. */

setExpanded.description:
/** Set the expanded state of this rowNode. Pass `true` to expand and `false` to collapse.
     */

setDataValue.description:
/** Replaces the value on the `rowNode` for the specified column. When complete,
     * the grid will refresh the rendered cell on the required row only.
     *
     * @param colKey The column where the value should be updated
     * @param newValue The new value
     * @param eventSource The source of the event
     * @returns `True` if the value was changed, otherwise `False`.
     */

resetQuickFilterAggregateText.description:
/** The first time `quickFilter` runs, the grid creates a one-off string representation of the row.
     * This string is then used for the quick filter instead of hitting each column separately.
     * When you edit, using grid editing, this string gets cleared down.
     * However if you edit without using grid editing, you will need to clear this string down for the row to be updated with the new values.
     * Otherwise new values will not work with the `quickFilter`. */

isSelected.description:
/** Returns:
     * - `true` if node is selected,
     * - `false` if the node isn't selected
     * - `undefined` if it's partially selected (group where not all children are selected). */

depthFirstSearch.description: /** Perform a depth-first search of this node and its children. */

setSelected.description:
/** Select (or deselect) the node.
     * @param newValue -`true` for selection, `false` for deselection.
     * @param clearSelection - If selecting, then passing `true` will select the node exclusively (i.e. NOT do multi select). If doing deselection, `clearSelection` has no impact.
     * @param suppressFinishActions - Pass `true` to prevent the `selectionChanged` from being fired. Note that the `rowSelected` event will still be fired.
     */
